episodes.title: Opening Statements in GA v. Chloe Driver. Cult Baby Murder Trial
episodes.description:
Opening statements are set to begin in the case against Chloe Driver, 24, who has pleaded not guilty because of insanity for multiple charges, including malice murder, in the Dec. 2020 death of her daughter, Hannah. While responding to a 911 call, police discovered Chloe and Hannah in a bedroom, both suffering from stab wounds.

The fatal incident occurred on Dec. 8, 2020, in the Mountain View subdivision of Cherokee County.
Upon arrival, police found Chloe Driver and her daughter in an upstairs bedroom; the daughter later died at the hospital.
Driver, who was 20 at the time of the charge, has entered a plea of guilty due to reasons of insanity.
She is facing charges of malice murder, two counts of felony murder, aggravated assault, and cruelty to children.
